; Ingest-netting contract (StackSafeNegation.md sec 5.0/5.5, Open Question
; 3 -- decided 2026-07-11): per batch, each explicit vector is deduplicated
; and the adds-intersect-removes set annihilates (dropped from BOTH sides,
; presence unchanged). This case pins multiplicity-insensitivity: duplicate
; ops within one batch are meaningless, so excess retractions can never
; outvote an add ({+x,-x,-x} is a no-op, not a removal) and excess adds can
; never outvote a retraction ({+y,+y,-y} is a no-op, not an add). Both
; polarities are exercised against absent AND present rows, with single-op
; control batches proving genuine adds/removes still land.
; The owner's normative framing (OQ3 sign-off): the intersection has NO
; effect on IDB state through the explicit channel -- the row keeps exactly
; the presence the rest of the program can prove for it. The second message
; `other` gives s(X) an alternate derivation, so an annihilating m-pair
; must neither kill a row `other` holds up nor resurrect one `other` drops
; in the same batch.
#message m(i32 X) @differential.
#message other(i32 X) @differential.

#local s(i32 X).

#query out(free i32 X).

s(X) : m(X).
s(X) : other(X).
out(X) : s(X).
